From the Easter news: „N. Fr. Pr.“: Dr. Lechner „Small-Stateness“;

               in many ways a brilliant essay; Harnack: „Religion in the World War“;

               from this above all that the Church accepted the inevitability of war between peoples already in the fourth century; Lujo Brentano: „A Proposal in the Question of Raw Materials After the War“

Nachträglich von Sophie  (K.):
              No correspondence from Sophie Guttmann is known to survive from before 1938. 
              habe auch Butter geschickt, legt Rechnung ausschließlich der Ostersendung, kündigt die baldige Absendung des nächsten Paketes an;

To Wilhelm (letter):
we had been prepared for this answer from the very beginning and thus only ask about when we can and are allowed to come to the grave and add a note that I ask be filled out so that I can finally settle the debts;
ask him about the sum that I could send in as a payment form in order to buy eggs and butter, we also invite him to come see us in May at our place in Vienna or somewhere else.
